sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K118005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andrew Hall
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding sequence of crtI from Pantoea ananatis (formerly Erwinia uredovora) (Accession number D90087) preceded by an E. coli synthetic ribosome binding site (rbs). It encodes phytoene dehydrogenase, part of the carotenoid biosynthesis pathway, which converts Phytoene to Lycopene.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
The native crtI sequence contains two internal PstI sites. Primers crtImutf1 and crtImutf2 were ordered so that the MABEL protocol (invented for this purpose) could be used to remove these sites. The mutagenic primers were as follows:
* crtImutf1: gtt tac agt aag gtt gcc
* crtImutf2: agt aac tct ctg ttt gtg c
In both cases, the PstI site CTGCAG was converted to CTGCAA, a silent mutation.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: rbs: Escherichia coli JM109 genomic DNA. crtI: Pantoea ananatis genomic DNA

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K118014
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Andrew Hall
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is the coding sequence of ''crtE'' from ''Pantoea ananatis'' (formerly ''Erwinia uredovora'') (Accession number D90087). It encodes geranylgeranyl pyrophosphate synthase, part of the carotenoid biosynthesis pathway, which converts farnesyl diphosphate to geranylgeranyl diphosphate.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The ''crtE'' BioBrick (BBa_I742151) had to be transferred from the non-compliant BABEL vector to a compliant pSB1A2 vector.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The synthetic ribosome binding site was added by fusion PCR to the ''crtE'' gene, which was amplified from ''Pantoea ananatis'' DSMZ 30080 (ATCC 19321) genomic DNA.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K152003
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: David Johnston Monje
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: crtE from Erwinia uredovora with a rbs preceeding it. This gene codes for lycopene cyclase which is the third step in the beta carotene synthesis pathway. In combination with CrtE and B, this works to produce lycopene, a red, antioxidant, carotenoid.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: We needed to use site directed mutagenesis to add the SpeI site after the stop codon.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The plasmid pUC-EUY which was sent to us by Ethan Johnson on iGEM Minnesota team timebomb.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: B-carotene
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Expresses B-carotene monooxygenase on a constitutive promotor
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Christian Kurtzhals
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription:
This generator expresses a beta-carotene 15,15'-monooxygenase,on a constitutive promotor, that catalyses retinal production from beta-carotene via the following reaction:
beta-carotene + O2 = 2 retinal
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The brick requires B-carotene supply to function. This can either be supplied externally, or alternatively the BBa_K274210 B-carotene generator will induce full B-carotene synthesis in E. coli.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The ninaB gene was originally cloned from drosophila melanogaster, and cDNA was aquired for production of the biobrick from the Drosophila Genome Ressource Center. Promotor+rbs brick BBa_J13002 and terminator BBa_B0015 were used.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: Note: the crtI coding sequence contains 2 PstI sites. sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: HMG-CoA-R
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Leonard Sebastian Fresenborg
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a truncated version of the 3-Hydroxy-3-Methyl-Glutaryl-Coenzyme-A-Reductase (HMG-CoA-R) from ''Saccharomyces cerevisiae''. It catalyses the reaction of 3-Hydroxy-3-Methyl-Glutaryle-Coenzyme-A to Mevalonate which occurs in the Mevalonate Pathway to Isopentylpyrophosphate which is the Precurser of all Isoprenoides. The enzyme is naturally a membrane bound enzyme. The membrane anchor is situated N-terminal. This region is also essential for the degradational control of the enzyme. By deleting the N-terminal part to Aminoacid (inclusive) the enzyme is expected to be water soluble and deregulated.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
The truncation was done according to the following publication:
[[http://aem.asm.org/content/76/19/6449.short|Rico, Pardo, Orejas: 'Enhanced Production of a Plant Monoterpene by Overexpression of the 3-Hydroxy-3-Methylglutaryl Conenzyme A Reductase Catalytic Domain in Saccharomyces cerevisiae'; Applied and Enviromental Microbiology; Vol 76 p. 6449-6454; 2010]]
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: The original source of this part is the genome of Saccharomyces cerevisiae. We obtained the sequence by de novo synthesis. For that we used data from the [[http://www.yeastgenome.org/|Saccharomyes Genome Database]]. We inserted some calm mutations to avoid conflicts with the Cloning Standard 10.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K152005
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Promoterless Synthetic Operon of CrtE,B,I,Y and GFP
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: David Johnston Monje
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This operon provides the full set of bacterial open reading frames necessary for beta carotene production with a GFP and termination stop signals tacked on at the end for good measure! crtE,B,I,Y coding regions from Erwinia uredovora each with a rbs preceeding the open reading frame. Likewise, the RBS-GFP-Term from biobrick BBa_E0240 is included on the end to provide a visual signal affirming transcription of preceeding 4 genes. There is no promoter on this construct, and after this GFP biobrick, no more genes can be added.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes: The synthetic operon needed a transcriptional termination signal, as well as GFP to visualize complete transcript production, so BBa_E0240 was used. No more genes can be added to this operon with this GFP on the end.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: This operon is made from biobricks BBa_K152001 - BBa_K152003, the biobrick BBa_K118005 which was sent to us by iGEM Edinburg, and BBa_E0240.
